
[1]greedy

   GREE'DY, a. [L. gradior,and probably signifies reaching forward.]

   1. Having a keen appetite for food or drink; ravenous; voracious; very
   hungry; followed by of; as a lion that is greedy of his prey. Ps.17.

   2. Having a keen desire of any thing; eager to obtain; as greedy of
   gain.
